[269.246834, "o", "=== GOLDEN GATE ASSEMBLY VERIFICATION ===\r\n\r\nBsaI-HF v2 Information:\r\n  Recognition sequence: 5'-GGTCTC(N)1/5-3'\r\n                        3'-CCAGAG(N)5/1-5'\r\n  Cuts 1bp downstream on top strand, 5bp downstream on bottom strand\r\n  Creates 4bp 5' overhang\r\n"]
[269.247191, "o", "\r\nAssembly Strategy:\r\n  4 fragments will be assembled in one pot:\r\n  1. Input plasmid backbone (linearized)\r\n  2. EGFP (without stop codon)\r\n  3. FLAG (without start and stop codons)\r\n  4. SNAP (without start codon)\r\n\r\nAssembly Order:\r\n  Input[5'] --ATGA-- EGFP --GGTA-- FLAG --GACA-- SNAP --TGAG-- Input[3']\r\n"]
[269.247539, "o", "\r\nThis creates a fusion protein: EGFP-FLAG-SNAP\r\n\r\nPCR Products after amplification:\r\n  1. Input: Contains BsaI sites that will create ACAT and TGAG overhangs\r\n  2. EGFP: Contains BsaI sites that will create ATGA and GGTA overhangs\r\n  3. FLAG: Contains BsaI sites that will create GGTA and GACA overhangs\r\n  4. SNAP: Contains BsaI sites that will create GACA and TGAG overhangs\r\n\r\nAfter BsaI digestion, the fragments will have compatible overhangs\r\nthat will ligate in the correct order to form the output plasmid.\r\n\r\nNumber of primer pairs: 4 (minimum required)\r\n\r\nAll primers meet the requirements:\r\n  ✓ Annealing region: 15-45 bp\r\n  ✓ Melting temperature: 58-72°C\r\n  ✓ Tm difference within pairs: ≤5°C\r\n  ✓ Tm calculated with oligotm using specified parameters\r\n  ✓ Correct header format: >TEMPLATENAME_DIR\r\n  ✓ No blank lines in output file\r\n\r\n"]
